---

### Step 2 — `packages/shared/package.json`

Add one entry to `"exports"`:

```json
"./theme": {
  "types": "./src/theme.ts",
  "import": "./src/theme.ts"
}
```

Insert it alongside the existing `"./model"`, `"./git"`, etc. entries.

---

### Step 3 — `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` (full rewrite)

Key changes from the current file:
1. Import `BuiltInThemeName`, `ThemePreference`, `BUILT_IN_THEMES`, `resolveTheme` from `@t3tools/shared/theme`.
2. Keep `STORAGE_KEY = "t3code:theme"` (same key, expand valid values).
3. Add **migration** in `getStored()`: old `"light"` → `"t3-light"`, old `"dark"` → `"t3-dark"`, old `"system"` → `"system"`, anything unrecognized → `"system"`.
4. Replace the old `applyTheme(theme: Theme, ...)` with a new version that:
   - Calls `resolveTheme(pref, getSystemDark())` to get the concrete `BuiltInTheme`
   - Toggles `.dark` class: `el.classList.toggle("dark", theme.isDark)`
   - Sets `el.style.colorScheme = theme.colorScheme`
   - Iterates `CSS_VAR_MAP` (a `Record<keyof ThemeColorTokens, string>` defined in this file) and calls `el.style.setProperty(cssVar, value)` for every token
5. Define `CSS_VAR_MAP` mapping camelCase token keys → CSS var names (e.g., `background` → `"--background"`, `sidebar` → `"--sidebar"`, `statusBar` → `"--status-bar"`, etc.)
6. Update the `ThemeSnapshot` type to `{ pref: ThemePreference; systemDark: boolean }`.
7. Update `useTheme()` to return:
   - `theme: ThemePreference` (the raw stored preference, including "system")
   - `resolvedTheme: BuiltInThemeName` (the concrete resolved name)
   - `resolvedThemeData: BuiltInTheme` (the full theme object, for swatches etc.)
   - `setTheme: (next: ThemePreference) => void`
8. The module-level `applyTheme(getStored())` call is kept (line ~45) — runs synchronously on module load before first React paint, preventing flash.

`CSS_VAR_MAP` (defined in the file, not exported from shared):
```ts
const CSS_VAR_MAP: Record<keyof ThemeColorTokens, string> = {
  background: "--background",
  foreground: "--foreground",
  card: "--card",
  cardForeground: "--card-foreground",
  popover: "--popover",
  popoverForeground: "--popover-foreground",
  primary: "--primary",
  primaryForeground: "--primary-foreground",
  secondary: "--secondary",
  secondaryForeground: "--secondary-foreground",
  muted: "--muted",
  mutedForeground: "--muted-foreground",
  accent: "--accent",
  accentForeground: "--accent-foreground",
  destructive: "--destructive",
  destructiveForeground: "--destructive-foreground",
  border: "--border",
  input: "--input",
  ring: "--ring",
  info: "--info",
  infoForeground: "--info-foreground",
  success: "--success",
  successForeground: "--success-foreground",
  warning: "--warning",
  warningForeground: "--warning-foreground",
  sidebar: "--sidebar",
  sidebarForeground: "--sidebar-foreground",
  editor: "--editor",
  editorForeground: "--editor-foreground",
  terminal: "--terminal",
  terminalForeground: "--terminal-foreground",
  statusBar: "--status-bar",
  statusBarForeground: "--status-bar-foreground",
};
```

The `subscribe` function keeps the same `storage` + `matchMedia` listeners as today — no changes needed there.

---

### Step 4 — `apps/web/src/components/ThemeProvider.tsx` (new file)

A thin React component that:
- Calls `useTheme()` (subscribes to the external store, keeps DOM in sync)
- Renders `children` — no JSX wrapper element

```tsx
import { useTheme } from "../hooks/useTheme";

export function ThemeProvider({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  useTheme(); // subscribes and keeps DOM in sync via useEffect inside hook
  return <>{children}</>;
}
```

---

### Step 5 — `apps/web/src/router.ts` (modify Wrap)

Add `ThemeProvider` to the existing provider stack. Current Wrap:
```tsx
Wrap: ({ children }) =>
  createElement(QueryClientProvider, { client: queryClient },
    createElement(StoreProvider, null, children))
```

New:
```tsx
import { ThemeProvider } from "./components/ThemeProvider";
// ...
Wrap: ({ children }) =>
  createElement(QueryClientProvider, { client: queryClient },
    createElement(StoreProvider, null,
      createElement(ThemeProvider, null, children)))
```

This guarantees `applyTheme` runs via the external store's `subscribe` before any child renders.

---

### Step 6 — `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` (new file)

```tsx
import { BUILT_IN_THEMES, type BuiltInThemeName, type ThemePreference } from "@t3tools/shared/theme";
import { useTheme } from "../hooks/useTheme";

const THEME_OPTIONS: Array<{ value: ThemePreference; label: string; description: string }> = [
  { value: "system", label: "System", description: "Match your OS appearance setting." },
  { value: "t3-light", label: "T3 Light", description: "Clean light interface." },
  { value: "t3-dark", label: "T3 Dark", description: "Classic dark interface." },
  { value: "t3-midnight", label: "T3 Midnight", description: "OLED-optimised pure black." },
];

function ThemeSwatch({ themeName }: { themeName: BuiltInThemeName }) {
  const { colors } = BUILT_IN_THEMES[themeName];
  return (
    <div className="flex gap-1 items-center" aria-hidden>
      <span
        className="h-4 w-4 rounded-sm border border-black/10"
        style={{ backgroundColor: colors.background }}
      />
      <span
        className="h-4 w-4 rounded-sm"
        style={{ backgroundColor: colors.primary }}
      />
      <span
        className="h-4 w-4 rounded-sm"
        style={{ backgroundColor: colors.sidebar }}
      />
    </div>
  );
}

export function ThemeSelector() {
  const { theme, setTheme } = useTheme();

  return (
    <div className="space-y-2" role="radiogroup" aria-label="Theme preference">
      {THEME_OPTIONS.map((option) => {
        const selected = theme === option.value;
        const swatchName =
          option.value === "system" ? null : (option.value as BuiltInThemeName);

        return (
          <button
            key={option.value}
            type="button"
            role="radio"
            aria-checked={selected}
            className={`flex w-full items-center justify-between rounded-lg border px-3 py-2 text-left transition-colors ${
              selected
                ? "border-primary/60 bg-primary/8 text-foreground"
                : "border-border bg-background text-muted-foreground hover:bg-accent"
            }`}
            onClick={() => setTheme(option.value)}
          >
            <span className="flex flex-col gap-0.5">
              <span className="text-sm font-medium">{option.label}</span>
              <span className="text-xs">{option.description}</span>
            </span>
            <span className="flex items-center gap-3">
              {swatchName && <ThemeSwatch themeName={swatchName} />}
              {selected && (
                <span className="rounded bg-primary/14 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-primary">
                  Active
                </span>
              )}
            </span>
          </button>
        );
      })}
    </div>
  );
}
```

---

### Step 7 — `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` (modify)

1. Remove the `THEME_OPTIONS` constant (lines 25–41) — no longer needed.
2. Remove the `resolvedTheme` destructure from `useTheme()` (or keep if still displayed).
3. Import `ThemeSelector` from `../components/ThemeSelector`.
4. In the Appearance `<section>`, replace the entire radio group (`<div role="radiogroup">...</div>` and the `{THEME_OPTIONS.map(...)}` block, plus the "Active theme:" paragraph) with `<ThemeSelector />`.

The section heading and description (`<h2>Appearance</h2>` etc.) are preserved.

---

## How Inline CSS Vars Override the Static `:root` Rules

- CSS custom properties defined via `element.style.setProperty("--foo", val)` (inline style) have higher cascade priority than any stylesheet rule, including `:root { --foo: ... }`.
- The `@variant dark { ... }` block inside `:root` continues to work for Tailwind `dark:` utility classes (it only affects how Tailwind generates selectors, not the CSS var values we set inline).
- The static `:root` vars in `index.css` become the no-JS fallback (they match the t3-light default).
- `applyTheme(getStored())` executes synchronously at module load time, before React mounts, so there is zero flash.

---

## Migration Path (localStorage)

`getStored()` in `useTheme.ts` handles old values:
- `"light"` → `"t3-light"`
- `"dark"` → `"t3-dark"`
- `"system"` → `"system"`
- anything else → `"system"` (default)

The same `"t3code:theme"` storage key is reused — no need for a new versioned key.

---

## Verification

```bash
# 1. Type-check everything
bun typecheck

# 2. Lint check
bun lint

# 3. Manual smoke test
#    - Open Settings → Appearance
#    - Should see 4 option rows: System, T3 Light, T3 Dark, T3 Midnight
#    - T3 Light and T3 Dark rows show 3 color swatches
#    - Selecting any theme immediately updates the entire app's colors
#    - Refresh — selected theme persists from localStorage
#    - Open DevTools → Computed → <html> element should show inline --background,
#      --primary, --sidebar, --status-bar etc. matching the selected theme
#    - System option follows OS dark/light mode toggle in real time
#    - Switching between themes has no visible flash (no-transitions suppression)
```

