## How Inline CSS Vars Override the Static `:root` Rules

- CSS custom properties defined via `element.style.setProperty("--foo", val)` (inline style) have higher cascade priority than any stylesheet rule, including `:root { --foo: ... }`.
- The `@variant dark { ... }` block inside `:root` continues to work for Tailwind `dark:` utility classes (it only affects how Tailwind generates selectors, not the CSS var values we set inline).
- The static `:root` vars in `index.css` become the no-JS fallback (they match the t3-light default).
- `applyTheme(getStored())` executes synchronously at module load time, before React mounts, so there is zero flash.

---

## Migration Path (localStorage)

`getStored()` in `useTheme.ts` handles old values:
- `"light"` → `"t3-light"`
- `"dark"` → `"t3-dark"`
- `"system"` → `"system"`
- anything else → `"system"` (default)

The same `"t3code:theme"` storage key is reused — no need for a new versioned key.

