# Custom Theme System for T3 Code

## Context

The app currently has only a binary light/dark/system theme toggle stored in `localStorage["t3code:theme"]`, controlled by toggling a `.dark` class on `<html>`. All colors are CSS custom properties defined in `apps/web/src/index.css` under `:root` with a `@variant dark` override block.

The task adds a named theme system with 3 built-in palettes ("t3-light", "t3-dark", "t3-midnight") — each carrying concrete color tokens for background, foreground, accent, sidebar, editor, terminal, and status bar. The selected theme is persisted to localStorage and applied by writing CSS custom properties directly as inline styles on `document.documentElement`, which overrides the static `:root` CSS rules. The `.dark` class is still toggled (for Tailwind `dark:` utilities). A theme selector component with color swatches replaces the existing radio buttons in Settings.

No new dependencies. No build config changes.

